OL,3,CMum diagnosed with cancer when
OL,4,Cpregnant says she's lucky to be alive
OL,6,FDoctors quickly performed major life-
OL,7,Fsaving surgery, removing the tumour
OL,8,Fand fitting a temporary stoma.
OL,10,F"I had a central line in my neck where
OL,11,Fthey put the medication," Nikki said.
OL,13,F"I was on a drip feed for the first
OL,14,Ffew days.
OL,16,F"Then we had physio to move me around
OL,17,Fin the bed, get me sitting up,
OL,18,Flearning to walk again, it was really
OL,19,Ftough."
OL,21,FWeeks later Nikki was allowed home.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/5
