OL,3,CMum diagnosed with cancer when
OL,4,Cpregnant says she's lucky to be alive
OL,6,F"When I left hospital I then went to
OL,7,Fmy mum's house for another two weeks
OL,8,Fto recover and I had the support of my
OL,9,Fsister to help me on and off a commode
OL,10,Fand change my stoma bag.
OL,12,F"And then the children would come in
OL,13,Fthe evening and I'd have the pillow on
OL,14,Fmy lap and Connie would be put on me
OL,15,Fand I'd feed her as much as I could
OL,16,Fand it was really tough."
OL,18,FAfter undergoing three months of
OL,19,Fchemotherapy, Nikki could finally
OL,20,Fstart to return to normal life.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/5
